  <data key="d16">strong_textual_inference</data>
  <data key="d17">As stated above ( II-II:92:2 ), moral acts take their species from their end. Now the end of an oath is the confirmation of a human assertion. To this confirmation falsehood is opposed: since an assertion is confirmed by being firmly shown to be true ; and thi</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_doctrinal</data>
</edge>
