  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q100.a002.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">the altar?" Accordingly we must answer that to receive money for the spiritual grace of the sacraments , is the sin of simony, which cannot be excused by any custom whatever, since "custom does not prevail over natural or divine law " [Cap. Cum tanto, de Consuetud.; cf. I-II:97:3 . No</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_doctrinal</data>
</edge>
