  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q082.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">Devotion is derived from "devote" [The Latin 'devovere' means 'to vow ']; wherefore those persons are said to be "devout" who, in a way, devote themselves to God , so as to subject themselves wholly to Him. Hence in olde</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
