  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q082.a002.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It belongs to the same virtue , to will to do something, and to have the will ready to do it, because both acts have the same object. For this reason the Philosopher says (Ethic. v, 1): "It is justice whereby men both wi</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
