  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q082.a004.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">The direct and principal effect of devotion is the spiritual joy of the mind , though sorrow is its secondary and indirect effect. For it has been stated ( Article 3 ) that devotion is caused by a twofold consideration: </data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
