  <data key="d8">II-II q.83 — Prayer</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q083.a016</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.83 a.16 — Do sinners impetrate anything from God by praying?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q083.a016.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">In the sinner, two things are to be considered: his nature which God loves, and the sin which He hates . Accordingly when a sinner prays for something as sinner, i.e. in accordance with a sinful desire, God hears him not</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q083" target="st.ii-ii.q083.a017" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q083.contains.st.ii-ii.q083.a017">
