  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q083.a017</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.83 a.17 — The different kinds of prayer</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q083.a017.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">Three conditions are requisite for prayer . First, that the person who prays should approach God Whom he prays : this is signified in the word " prayer ," because prayer is "the raising up of one's mind to God ." The sec</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
