  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">As Augustine says (De Verb. Dom. Serm. cxiii), "shouldst thou plunder one weaker than thyself and give some of the spoil to the judge, if he should pronounce in thy favor, such is the force of justice that even thou woul</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
