  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q088.a005.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">As stated above ( II-II:81:1 ad 1 ), every act of virtue belongs to religion or latria by way of command, in so far as it is directed to the reverence of God which is the proper end of latria . Now the direction of other</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
