  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q088.a007.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">The manner in which a thing is solemnized depends on its nature [conditio]: thus when a man takes up arms he solemnizes the fact in one way, namely, with a certain display of horses and arms and a concourse of soldiers, </data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
