  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">uch a case comes under neither law nor vow . Now anything morally evil or hurtful is incompatible with the matter of an oath : for if it be morally evil it is opposed to justice , and if it be hurtful it is contrary to judgment. Therefore an oath likewise admits of dispensation.</data>
