  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">As stated above ( II-II:81:5 ), religion is a moral virtue . Now every moral virtue observes a mean, as stated above ( I-II:64:1 ). Therefore a twofold vice is opposed to a moral virtue . One by way of excess, the other </data>
