  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">As stated above ( Article 1 ; Q92,94 ), superstition denotes undue divine worship. Now a thing pertains to the worship of God in two ways: in one way, it is something offered to God ; as a sacrifice, an oblation, or some</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q095" target="st.ii-ii.q095.a003" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q095.contains.st.ii-ii.q095.a003">
