  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q095.a008</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.95 a.8 — Divination by lots</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q095.a008.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">As stated above ( Article 3 ), sortilege consists, properly speaking, in doing something, that by observing the result one may come to the knowledge of something unknown. If by casting lots one seeks to know what is to b</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q095.a001" target="concept.divination" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q095.a001.treated_in.concept.divination">
