  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.divination</data>
  <data key="d12">Divination</data>
  <data key="d13">sin_type</data>
  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q095-a008-treated-in-concept-divination-st-ii-ii-q095-a008-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q095.a008.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">one, it is called "sortilege of consultation"; if one seeks to know what is going to happen, it is called "sortilege of divination ." Now the actions of man that are required for sortilege and their results are not subject to the dispositions of the stars. Wherefore if anyone practicing so</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q096" target="concept.superstitious_observance" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q096.treated_in.concept.superstitious_observance">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.ii-ii.q096.treated_in.concept.superstitious_observance</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q096</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.96 — Superstition in observances</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.superstitious_observance</data>
  <data key="d12">Superstitious Observance</data>
  <data key="d13">sin_type</data>
  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q096-treated-in-concept-superstitious-observance-st-ii-ii-q096-a001-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q096.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">The magic art is both unlawful and futile. It is unlawful, because the means it employs for acquiring knowledge have not in themselves the power to cause science, consisting as they do in gazing certain shapes, and muttering certain strange words, and so forth</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q096" target="st.ii-ii.q096.a001" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q096.contains.st.ii-ii.q096.a001">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q096.contains.st.ii-ii.q096.a001</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q096</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.96 — Superstition in observances</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q096.a001</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.96 a.1 — Observances for acquiring knowledge, which are prescribed by the magic art</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q096.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">The magic art is both unlawful and futile. It is unlawful, because the means it employs for acquiring knowledge have not in themselves the power to cause science, consisting as they do in gazing certain shapes, and mutte</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q096" target="st.ii-ii.q096.a002" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q096.contains.st.ii-ii.q096.a002">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q096.contains.st.ii-ii.q096.a002</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q096</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.96 — Superstition in observances</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q096.a002</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.96 a.2 — Observances for causing alterations in certain bodies</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q096.a002.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">In things done for the purpose of producing some bodily effect we must consider whether they seem able to produce that effect naturally : for if so it will not be unlawful to do so, since it is lawful to employ natural c</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q096" target="st.ii-ii.q096.a003" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q096.contains.st.ii-ii.q096.a003">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q096.contains.st.ii-ii.q096.a003</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q096</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.96 — Superstition in observances</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q096.a003</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.96 a.3 — Observances practiced in fortune-telling</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q096.a003.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">Men attend to all these observances, not as causes but as signs of future events, good or evil . Nor do they observe them as signs given by God , since these signs are brought forward, not on divine authority, but rather</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q096" target="st.ii-ii.q096.a004" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q096.contains.st.ii-ii.q096.a004">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q096.contains.st.ii-ii.q096.a004</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q096</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.96 — Superstition in observances</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q096.a004</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.96 a.4 — Wearing sacred words at the neck</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q096.a004.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">In every incantation or wearing of written words, two points seem to demand caution. The first is the thing said or written, because if it is connected with invocation of the demons it is clearly superstitious and unlawf</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q096.a001" target="concept.magical_observance" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q096.a001.treated_in.concept.magical_observance">
